name: Bigsby's Folly
description: Wine, small plates, great crack bacon

name: Lustre Pearl
description: Not the iced Irish coffee though. Drinks.

name: Ratio Beerworks
description: Domestica is good. Dog-friendly, mist in summer, cheap. Order food from Shake Shack or Barcelona. Good music.

name: Uchi
description: Sushi, pricey and you'll leave hungry

name: Modern Market
description: Grubhub. Soup, sandwiches, salads, grain bowls. Healthy and delicious.

name: Temaki Den
description: Sushi, pricey. Hand rolls weren't rolled, didn't sit well, not worth it.

name: Il Posto
description: Try the Cabin in the Woods drink. Excellent cocktails and wine, charcuterie. $. Tuesday is less busy.

name: Red Square Euro Bistro
description: Russian food and vodka. Try the Jewel vodka, the honey dessert, and the borscht.

name: Spice Room
description: Indian. Nice lunch specials, complimentary papadums.

name: Port Side
description: Coffee, drinks, brunch, snacks (outside). Nice, inexpensive.

name: Number Thirty-eight
description: Drinks, food, live music, dog-friendly. Reservations.

name: The Walnut Room
description: Best Reubens, drinks with fresh ingredients, dog patio

name: Ted's Montana Grill
description: Good bison at reasonable prices but slow service and a bit country

name: Adrift
description: Tiki bar. Reservations suggested, sit indoors, stick to frozen drinks.

name: Ali Baba Grill
description: Turkish coffee, lunch specials, good gyros. Yahya's is better overall.

name: Citron Bistro
description: Greek. Great service, reasonable prices, not pretentious, good food, gluten-free options.

name: Rare Finds
description: Nice antiques, imported furniture, reasonably priced

name: Tupelo Honey
description: Good southern brunch. Chicken and waffles.

name: Indian Springs
description: Hot springs. Decent but not great for shared pool. Not very hot nor many minerals or amenities.

name: Mile High Flea Market
description: Cash only mostly. Bargains, mostly resale.

name: Butcher Block Cafe
description: Old school diner. Friendly, fast, reasonable prices, decent food. Maybe try for breakfast.

name: Bellota at the Source
description: Tacos at reasonable prices, good service, EPIC churros

name: Sir
description: Good cocktails. Try the espresso martini.

name: Il Porcellino
description: Deli with meat, soup, sandwiches. Busy, small, may take some time.

name: Denver Cat Company
description: Cat cafe with adoption. Varies based on cat population.

name: The Bronze Empire
description: Chinese hot pots cooked at your table. Try the fried ice cream dessert.

name: School House
description: Good weekend brunch, drinks, dog-friendly patio

name: Bacon Social House
description: Breakfast, brunch, drinks, dog-friendly patio. Bloody Marys.

name: Cafe Miriam
description: Coffee, pastries, brunch. Good chai, great pastries. Outdoor patio (dog-friendly). Closed Mondays.

name: Fox Run Cafe
description: Breakfast, good coffee, alcoholic drinks. Friendly, small dog-friendly patio. Reasonable prices. Get there by 11 for breakfast burrito.

name: Sprouts
description: Grocery. Nice deli (deli closes before store).

name: Lula Rose General Store
description: Coffee, breakfast (good burritos), plants, good dirty chai

name: Good Times
description: Shakes, custard, burgers. Paw Bender for dogs. Drive-through.

name: Chocolate Lab
description: Delicious chocolate drinks, but bartender is unfriendly

name: Trattoria Stella
description: Dog-friendly patio. Delicious weekend brunch after 10. Reasonable prices for Denver. Can bring coffee from Hooked on Colfax.

name: Saucy Bombay
description: Very reasonable prices, can taste sauces. SUPER fresh naan.

name: Zorba's
description: Greek food, breakfast. Real Irish coffees. Dog-friendly patio. Baked goods. 41 years in business.

name: Enzo's Pizza
description: GREAT thin crust pizza. Closed Mon/Tue. Recommend take-out.

name: Tommy's Thai
description: Nice menu, lunch specials, reasonable prices. Best Thai in Denver. Great service.

name: Q House
description: Odd hours, a little pricey, good service, tasty food, good cocktails

name: Bastien's
description: Sugar steaks, sugar burgers. Good drinks and appetizers. Pricey but worth it. Reservations recommended.

name: Goosetown Tavern
description: Sandwiches, beer, mixed drinks. Sometimes live music. Limited food selection.

name: The Watering Bowl
description: Off-leash dog area, bar, indoor miniature golf

name: Cafe de France
description: Only tried on Grubhub but good for brunch

name: GB Fish & Chips
description: Really nice and fun, kinda punk

name: H&E Used Furniture
description: FAR better deals than similar stores, without sacrificing quality. Clean and friendly. Say hi to Sammy the dog.

name: Taste of India
description: Russian market in same parking lot

name: Molotov Kitschen
description: GREAT Ukrainian food and drinks. Expensive but worth it. Try the elk. Save room for dessert. Reservations recommended.

name: Champagne Tiger
description: Formerly Tom's Starlight. Food, brunch, cocktails, retro atmosphere.

name: Yianni's Gyros Place
description: Reasonable, friendly, good. Crispy fries don't get soggy.

name: Chubby Cattle
description: Good but $$$ and too much food. No reservations.

name: Jelly
description: Breakfast, donut bites. Popular, online waiting list. Pancakes, specials, gluten-free options.

name: The Abbey Tavern
description: Irish weekend brunch. Dark and cool. Try Irish breakfast.

name: Briar Patch
description: Food, microbrew beer, drinks. Dog porch. Try French toast or Reuben.

name: Yard House
description: Wide variety, good, by Paramount. Reasonable.

name: Sukiya Ramen
description: Only tried DoorDash but some of the best udon I have had
